properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued March 3 at 1:36AM MST until March 3 at 2:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph and gusts up to 65 mph. Areas
of blowing snow will create additional travel impacts along
Interstate 80 and 25 with slick roads and low visibilities.

* WHERE...Laramie Valley County.

* WHEN...Until 2 PM MST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel will be difficult
especially for lightweight, high profile vehicles and campers.
Blowing snow will create areas of low to limited visibility
along with slick to snow-covered roadways.
properties.instruction:
People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown
around or damaged by the wind.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON
